# Management Hub — environment & URL reference

**Fastest for Render:** copy all lines from repo root **`render.env`** (no `#` comments — safe bulk paste). Replace `YOUR_APPS_SCRIPT_API_KEY_FROM_SCRIPT_PROPERTIES` and `PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` / `CORS_ORIGINS` if your Render URL is not `hub-api.onrender.com`. Rotate `JWT_SECRET` after first deploy if you want your own secret.

Other templates:

- API local: `apps/api/.env` ← `apps/api/.env.example`
- Web local: `apps/web/.env.local` ← `apps/web/.env.local.example`

**Do not commit real secrets.** Placeholders in `render.env` are safe to commit.

---

## 1. URLs (grouped)

Use **HTTPS** in production. **No trailing slash** on API base URLs unless noted.

| Purpose | Variable(s) | Example / pattern |
|--------|-------------|-------------------|
| Public API (browser + sheet links) | `PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL` | `https://your-service.onrender.com` |
| Apps Script — main controller (`pull`, actions) | `GOOGLE_SHEET_APPS_SCRIPT_URL` | `https://script.google.com/macros/s/…/exec` |
| Apps Script — login / `sessionPing` (optional) | `GOOGLE_SHEET_LOGIN_APPS_SCRIPT_URL` | Same as above or a second deployment |
| Web → API (split hosting) | `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` | `https://your-service.onrender.com` or empty for same-origin |
| Web → Apps Script (browser session checks) | `NEXT_PUBLIC_JR_SHEET_APPS_SCRIPT_URL` | Same `/exec` as API sheet URL |
| Workers calendar (optional) | `NEXT_PUBLIC_JR_WORKERS_CALENDAR_APPS_SCRIPT_URL` | `https://script.google.com/macros/s/…/exec` |
| R2 / public files | `STORAGE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` | `https://files.yourdomain.com` or R2 public URL |
| Square checkout (invoice PDFs) | `INVOICE_SQUARE_CHECKOUT_URL` | `https://checkout.square.site/merchant/…` |

**Google Sheet (not an env var):** open your spreadsheet; the ID is the long string in:

`https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/<SHEET_ID>/edit`

Set `JR_SPREADSHEET_ID` in **Apps Script → Project settings → Script properties** (not in Nest `.env`).

